                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 813.00/896</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Guatemala</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-12-11T16:00:00-06:02">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 11, 1917, 4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>In an interview this afternoon President Cabrera said that Costa Rica and
                    Nicaragua cannot participate in the preliminary conference to be held here to
                    arrange program of proposed congress on union of Central American States and the
                    conference will not take place therefore. Evidently he is convinced that the
                    congress will itself not assemble until some more convenient season.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Leavell</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
